From cou.: 1 Welcome to the third Molecular BioSystems Emerging Investigators issue devoted to outstanding young scientists working at the chemical- and systems-biology interfaces.
From Soup: 1 All the contributors to this 2010 Emerging Investigators issue came highly-recommended as scientists at a relatively early stage in their careers whose work has the potential to influence future directions in chemical-genetics and systems biology.
 ###### 
From cou.: 2 All the contributors to this 2010 Emerging Investigators issue came highly-recommended as scientists at a relatively early stage in their careers whose work has the potential to influence future directions in chemical-genetics and systems biology.
From Soup: 2 The resulting issue comprises 25 articles: 3 reviews, 7 communications and 15 full papers. Taken together, the exciting science revealed in this issue spans the areas of proteomics, signalling, transport and chemical tools for probing biological systems.
 ###### 
From cou.: 3 The resulting issue comprises 25 articles: 3 reviews, 7 communications and 15 full papers. Taken together, the exciting science revealed in this issue spans the areas of proteomics, signalling, transport and chemical tools for probing biological systems.
From Soup: 3 I hope you enjoy this third Emerging Investigators issue in Molecular BioSystems. I would like to congratulate all the principal authors and their research teams for the exciting work published in this issue and to wish them every success in their future research!
